headline: Down 45%, Should You Buy the Dip on Intel?
summary: The semiconductor company has been largely left behind in the artificial intelligence (AI) infrastructure build-out mania, while its foundry ambitions have floundered.  Intel stock is down 45% in the last year.  Intel named a new CEO last month, tapping long-term industry vet Lip-Bu Tan to run the struggling company.
